		Aaron Malachi Mixon, III, medical products executive. Recipient Alumni Achievement award, Harvard Business School, 2007. Chairman board trustees Cleveland Clinic Foundation, Cleveland Institute Music.
		
       		



Background




III, Aaron Malachi Mixon, was born on May 22, 1940.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor, Harvard University, 1962. Master of Business Administration, Harvard University, 1968.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			President Invacare Corporation, Chief Executive Officer Elyria, Ohio, 1979—2010, chairman, since 1983. Board directors The Sherwin-Williams Company, since 1993, Park-Ohio Holdings Corporation, since 2008.
			
       			












Membership


			Chairman board trustees Cleveland Clinic Foundation, Cleveland Institute Music.
			
    			







Connections


			Married Barbara Weber. 2 children.
			
    			



